Commentary: edged and taken! And Shakib Al Hasan's glorious World Cup campaign comes to an end. Tried to cut this square, but beaten by the extra pace, and he leaves to a huge roar from the Bangladesh fans. Seven half-centuries can you believe it. Take a bow, Shakib. Take a bow. Ending the campaign with 606 runs - the third most in a single men's World Cup edition (Both Sachin and Hayden played double-digit games though)
